charls
------------------------------------------
CharLS is a C++ implementation of the JPEG-LS standard for lossless and
near-lossless image compression and decompression. JPEG-LS is a low-complexity
image compression standard that matches JPEG 2000 compression ratios.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libcharls-devel-2.4.2-1bl2
  libcharls2-2.4.2-1bl2
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cmake-4.1.3-1
  cygport-0.37.4-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/team-charls/charls

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/team-charls/charls/archive/refs/tags/2.4.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack charls-2.4.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./charls-2.4.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/charls-2.4.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/charls-2.4.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcharls2-2.4.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcharls-devel-2.4.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

